This is a drop in replacement singleton for the AjaxUtils singleton in the code!
There was this special construct in the old code which allowed inheritance from other singletons respectively their classes. That way I could split seldomly used functionality out codewise into their own classes (did the same with inheritance) to keep a separation of concerns between general implementation and browser specific quirks implementations. Thats also the reason why it was possible relatively quickly to drop a ton of browser specific code in next!

The replacement of the old AjaxUtils with the inherited PartialSubmitUtils happens in the constructor:

    constructor_: function() {
        this._callSuper("constructor_");
        //we replace the original class with our new implementation
        myfaces._impl.xhrCore._AjaxUtils = this;
    },

As you can see, the drop in replacement happens in the line myfaces._impl.xhrCore._AjaxUtils = this;

So what happens here is that I inherit from the AjaxUtils class and then replace the already existing Ajax Utils singletoin with the instance of the inheritance this is happening at code initialization time ans subsequently, later whenever AjaxUtils are called the code reverts to this singleton!

PS: If it works now for your usecase scenario, then we can merge, just give me the ok!

This should fix the issue from the js side. The main culprit was that behavior events added the key value pair from the issuing element (4606 patch), and then on the server side an action was triggered automatically

@volosied  @tandraschko please test this patch, for me this restores the wanted original behavior!
I guess @tandraschko your merge request now can be dropped if this works well!
